04:40.851 --> 04:45.189
it’s Michael.
Jules, it must be months, huh?

04:45.189 --> 04:51.028
l can't wait to talk to you.
I'm in Chicago at the Drake Hotel.

04:51.028 --> 04:55.032
Call me. 4:00 in the morning,
whatever. We gotta talk. Bye.

04:55.032 --> 04:59.203
- Who called? Man of the moment?
- No, the opposite.

04:59.203 --> 05:03.140
It's my Michael. Michael O'Neal.
Sounds desperate to talk to me.

05:03.140 --> 05:06.677
The wandering sportswriter.
Remind me about that one.

05:06.677 --> 05:08.178
Sophomore year at Brown...

05:08.178 --> 05:11.882
we had this one hot month.

05:11.882 --> 05:15.886
But you know me.
I got restless.

05:15.886 --> 05:19.556
So I get up the nerve
to break his heart...

05:19.556 --> 05:21.547
and he gives me this look.

05:22.926 --> 05:25.229
Then he said, ''The thing
that makes me want to cry is...

05:25.229 --> 05:28.565
I'm losing the best friend
I ever had.''

05:28.565 --> 05:32.403
At that moment,
I knew I tell the same way.

05:32.403 --> 05:36.407
So I cried for maybe
the third time in my entire life...

05:36.407 --> 05:38.075
kissed him...

05:38.075 --> 05:40.839
and we've been best friends
ever since.

05:42.079 --> 05:44.343
We've seen each other
through everything:

05:46.250 --> 05:48.252
losing jobs...

05:48.252 --> 05:50.754
losing parents, losing lovers.

05:50.754 --> 05:53.690
We've traveled all over.

05:53.690 --> 05:56.427
The best times of my life, maybe.

05:56.427 --> 06:00.597
Drinking and talking,
even if it's just over the phone.

06:00.597 --> 06:04.034
Go on. This is so moving.
Kindred spirits?

06:04.034 --> 06:07.697
He's nothing Like me.
He's Like you actually, only straight.

06:09.006 --> 06:12.576
I remember this one night
in Tucson six years ago.

06:12.576 --> 06:15.612
He takes a razor out
of this little shaving kit...

06:15.612 --> 06:18.615
cuts his finger, takes my hand,
does the same to me.

06:18.615 --> 06:21.952
- I'm gonna be sick.
- He says, ''Swear when we're 28...

06:21.952 --> 06:24.922
if we've never married,
we marry each other.''

06:24.922 --> 06:27.658
We never talked about it again.

06:27.658 --> 06:31.462
I don't know
what made me think of that.

06:31.462 --> 06:34.659
You're about to be 28
in three weeks, right?

06:35.799 --> 06:40.003
- How old is he?
- You think?

06:40.003 --> 06:42.801
Desperate to talk.

06:51.315 --> 06:52.748
Cheers.

06:55.352 --> 06:58.287
''Digital Answering System''
''Play''

