07:14.004 --> 07:17.508
- Good evening. The Drake Hotel.
- I'm calling for Michael O'Neal...

07:17.508 --> 07:20.602
- but since it's so late--
- One moment, please.

07:23.013 --> 07:24.446
Hello?

07:26.683 --> 07:29.853
You've been enrolled
in the Obscene caller of the Month Club.

07:29.853 --> 07:32.856
Hey, beautiful.
it’s so great to hear your voice.

07:32.856 --> 07:36.193
l miss you. I've been
calling you for over a month.

07:36.193 --> 07:38.028
I've been on a book tour.

07:38.028 --> 07:41.198
- I figured you were out of town.
- My machine eats all my messages.

07:41.198 --> 07:43.534
Or you're just averaging 30 days
to return a call.

07:43.534 --> 07:48.372
- it’s less when it's you.
- I have to ask you something important.

07:48.372 --> 07:50.374
lf you turn me down,
l don't know what I'll do.

07:50.374 --> 07:54.470
It I could just tell you
one thing first.

07:56.380 --> 07:59.550
This is probably going
to hand you...

07:59.550 --> 08:02.553
the biggest laugh
of your adult life...

08:02.553 --> 08:05.389
but I was thinking about you,
and I was remembering...

08:05.389 --> 08:10.394
this unbelievably insane night
we spent in Tucson...

08:10.394 --> 08:13.230
like a thousand years ago.

08:13.230 --> 08:15.566
- You probably won't remember this--
- Are you kidding?

08:15.566 --> 08:18.569
l think about that night
all the time.

08:18.569 --> 08:20.571
You do?

08:20.571 --> 08:23.907
But it's not why I called.

08:23.907 --> 08:25.409
It's not.

08:25.409 --> 08:28.503
l called because I met someone.

08:30.914 --> 08:32.582
That's great.

08:32.582 --> 08:37.754
You haven't really seen anybody
since that dingbat Jenny Lee, have you?

08:37.754 --> 08:39.423
You don't understand.

08:39.423 --> 08:42.426
I've never felt this way
about anybody.

08:42.426 --> 08:46.263
- She's all wrong for me.
- That's a good start.

08:46.263 --> 08:48.432
She's a junior
at the University of Chicago.

08:48.432 --> 08:51.602
She's 20. Her name's Kim.
You're gonna love her. She's beautiful.

08:51.602 --> 08:55.439
Her dad is this billionaire. He owns
the White Sox and some cable empire.

08:55.439 --> 08:58.108
I've always been uncomfortable
around rich people.

08:58.108 --> 09:01.778
- Sure.
- But they're not like that.

09:01.778 --> 09:06.283
They're such wonderful people.
Salt of the earth.

09:06.283 --> 09:08.547
So you've met her parents?

09:10.454 --> 09:13.787
Jules, we're getting married
this Sunday.

09:15.792 --> 09:18.226
- Hello?
- Michael--

09:20.297 --> 09:22.466
It's Wednesday night.

09:22.466 --> 09:24.635
How can you possibly
be getting married on Sunday?

09:24.635 --> 09:26.303
Actually, it starts tomorrow.

09:26.303 --> 09:29.306
it’s a four-day wedding
with all the traditional events...

09:29.306 --> 09:33.810
and 10 million people
flying in from all over the world.

09:33.810 --> 09:37.981
Aren't you working this weekend?
Is that responsible?

09:37.981 --> 09:43.487
The Sox are at home and Sports is
letting me do a profile on Frank Thomas.

09:43.487 --> 09:45.656
Wait.
What do you mean, irresponsible?

09:45.656 --> 09:48.250
Taking off a weekend
to get married?

09:50.160 --> 09:52.253
Jules, I'm scared.

09:53.997 --> 09:58.001
- Maybe we should talk about this.
- I need you.

09:58.001 --> 10:01.338
lf you can't come and hold my hand,
I'll never get through this.

10:01.338 --> 10:03.272
Please come.

10:05.676 --> 10:08.879
l can 't wait for you
to meet her.

10:08.879 --> 10:12.849
''United Airlines''
Listen, Jules.

10:12.849 --> 10:14.851
Let's stop for a drink.
You can take a later flight.

10:14.851 --> 10:18.689
I'm a busy girl. I've got four days
to break up a wedding...

10:18.689 --> 10:22.793
steal the bride's fellow,
and I haven't one clue how to do it.

10:22.793 --> 10:25.529
He adored me
for nine goddamn years.

10:25.529 --> 10:29.232
- I can see why.
- She has known him for five seconds.

10:29.232 --> 10:32.703
Plus, she's got billions of dollars,
and she's apparently perfect.

10:32.703 --> 10:37.140
So don't go feeling all sorry
for Miss Preteen Illinois.

10:39.543 --> 10:42.979
l can't lose him, George.
I'm going to bring him back.

10:45.048 --> 10:46.216
You give your hand to me

10:46.216 --> 10:49.052
You give your hand to me

10:49.052 --> 10:51.520
And then you say hello

10:52.589 --> 10:55.892
l can hardly speak

10:55.892 --> 10:59.396
My heart is beating so

10:59.396 --> 11:03.066
And anyone can tell

11:03.066 --> 11:06.236
You think you know me well

11:06.236 --> 11:09.603
But you don't know me

11:12.409 --> 11:16.580
No, you don't know the one

11:16.580 --> 11:20.250
Who dreams of you at night

11:20.250 --> 11:23.587
Wants to kiss your lips

11:23.587 --> 11:26.590
Wants to hold you tight

11:26.590 --> 11:29.926
l am just a friend

11:29.926 --> 11:33.597
That's all I've ever been

11:33.597 --> 11:37.363
- Can you believe I'm gonna do this?
- Not hardly.

11:52.616 --> 11:55.719
This just makes everything
so perfect.

11:55.719 --> 12:00.247
Since I've met Michael, all I've heard
is ''Julianne this'' and ''Julianne that.''

12:01.124 --> 12:03.092
I've never had a sister.

12:11.134 --> 12:13.570
I have this monstrous favor
to ask you.

12:13.570 --> 12:15.305
- Excuse me?
- My best friend...

12:15.305 --> 12:20.811
shattered her pelvis line dancing
in Abilene over spring break.

12:20.811 --> 12:23.279
- Be my maid of honor?
- What?

12:24.815 --> 12:29.619
Shouldn't you promote a bridesmaid
or someone you've known longer?

12:29.619 --> 12:33.156
My bridesmaids are my only two
female relatives under the age of 40...

12:33.156 --> 12:37.160
debutante sisters from Nashville
who are basically vengeful sluts.

12:37.160 --> 12:38.457
My exit!

12:41.364 --> 12:43.934
I have tour days
to make you my new best friend.

12:43.934 --> 12:46.994
It's time for you
to force yourself to get personal.

13:01.017 --> 13:03.687
- Do you like the color?
- I think it's beautiful.

13:03.687 --> 13:05.689
- Isn't that perfect for her?
- absolutely.

13:05.689 --> 13:08.692
This is going to be tighter.
You don't want those things to fall out.

13:08.692 --> 13:11.895
- It's beautiful.
- I'm not hurting you.

13:11.895 --> 13:16.800
I don't want her to trip,
so I'll take this up a tiny bit.

13:16.800 --> 13:19.166
Would you rather the daffodil?

13:21.238 --> 13:25.041
I thought the bridesmaids
all wore the same dress.

13:25.041 --> 13:29.068
Not you. You wouldn't be comfortable
unless you were distinctive.

13:31.715 --> 13:34.017
What else did he tell you?

13:34.017 --> 13:37.053
You hate weddings.
You never go.

13:37.053 --> 13:39.556
You're not up
for anything conventional...

13:39.556 --> 13:43.492
or anything that's assumed
to be a female priority...

13:44.728 --> 13:49.065
including marriage
or romance or even--

13:49.065 --> 13:50.657
Love?

13:52.569 --> 13:55.405
Michael and I were a wrong tip
right from the start.

13:55.405 --> 13:58.074
He said that too.

13:58.074 --> 14:02.412
I thought I was like you,
and proud to be...

14:02.412 --> 14:05.615
until I met rumpled,
smelly, old Michael.

14:05.615 --> 14:08.084
Then I found I was just
a sentimental schmuck...

14:08.084 --> 14:11.755
like all those flighty nitwits
I'd always pitied.

14:11.755 --> 14:13.746
It's funny, huh?

14:15.091 --> 14:17.685
l need a cigarette.

14:26.436 --> 14:28.438
George, how do you think I feel?

14:28.438 --> 14:31.107
all she does is talk
about her and Michael's future.

14:31.107 --> 14:36.079
- She's just so dreamy.
- Jules, pull yourself together.

14:36.079 --> 14:38.309
I don't know if I can do it.

14:40.216 --> 14:42.786
You want me to turn around
or something?

14:42.786 --> 14:46.552
Not the person I was expecting.

14:49.592 --> 14:52.220
I've seen you
a lot more naked than that.

14:54.464 --> 14:58.901
Things are different now.

15:02.639 --> 15:04.573
I guess so.

15:09.512 --> 15:12.649
You look really good...

15:12.649 --> 15:14.947
without your clothes on.

15:25.829 --> 15:27.262
She's toast.

15:29.332 --> 15:31.425
''Caution 2-Way Traffic''
''Exit''

15:36.172 --> 15:38.842
- Where is the honeymoon exactly?
- It depends.

15:38.842 --> 15:42.345
If San Antonio sweeps Sacramento,
we could start there.
''Chicago Hilton And Towers''

15:42.345 --> 15:44.848
Or Phoenix. Or depending
on the Indiana-Cleveland game--

15:44.848 --> 15:46.516
Garden spots, all.

15:46.516 --> 15:49.686
A swing of maybe 40 degrees Fahrenheit
represents a packing challenge...

15:49.686 --> 15:53.523
but there's tine food and cocktails
at a choice of Embassy Suites.

15:53.523 --> 15:57.660
it’s his career. I'm supportive.
I've been everywhere.

15:57.660 --> 16:01.798
I want to be with the man I love.
That's what makes it a honeymoon.

16:01.798 --> 16:07.771
He's lucky. One woman in a billion
could put up with his shit.

16:07.771 --> 16:11.007
The guy's a one-man festival
of idiosyncratic--

16:11.007 --> 16:13.676
You've been introduced
to the symphonic range--

16:13.676 --> 16:16.880
Of his snoring?
He says it's worse than ever.

16:16.880 --> 16:19.178
You know that snarfle one?

16:21.885 --> 16:25.981
Now it's got this phlegm-rattling thing
happening behind it.

16:33.563 --> 16:35.065
Earplugs work.

16:35.065 --> 16:38.268
- What about--
- Cigars in bed? I broke him of that.

16:38.268 --> 16:41.204
The bathroom's a swamp.
He wears Reeboks to dinner.

16:41.204 --> 16:45.008
He likes action movies.
He reads over my Shoulder.

16:45.008 --> 16:46.943
He loves karaoke bars...

16:46.943 --> 16:49.245
- and I can't carry a tune.
- Really?

16:49.245 --> 16:51.748
He sucks soup
through his front teeth.

16:51.748 --> 16:55.081
That's a trademark move.
Don't touch that one.

16:56.920 --> 16:59.354
But he sure can kiss.

17:01.591 --> 17:05.185
It's been a while.
I'm just gonna take your word on that.

17:10.767 --> 17:15.105
After two weeks
of cataloging all his faults...

17:15.105 --> 17:18.040
I made a command decision
that changed my life.

17:23.113 --> 17:24.646
I threw the list away.

17:24.646 --> 17:26.983
He's not a balance sheet.
He's Michael.

17:26.983 --> 17:29.085
Loving him means
loving all of him.

17:29.085 --> 17:30.887
Do you get nervous
in confined spaces?

17:30.887 --> 17:32.956
It's sweet of you
to want to be protective...

17:32.956 --> 17:36.759
but nothing ever could give me
one moment's pause about this marriage.

17:36.759 --> 17:40.991
- Do you become hysterical in confined--
- Except one.

17:42.132 --> 17:44.434
You. You're always
in his mind....

17:44.434 --> 17:46.769
this perfect creature
he loved for years.

17:46.769 --> 17:49.806
perfection can get wearing
after awhile.

17:49.806 --> 17:52.642
I'm not kidding. I had to face up
to my competitive drives.

17:52.642 --> 17:54.978
believe me, I've got them.

17:54.978 --> 17:58.314
Am I gonna be jealous of you
for the rest of my life?

17:58.314 --> 18:00.450
- Our paths will keep crossing.
- Space. of course.

18:00.450 --> 18:01.985
- He'll always talk about you.
- It's only natural.

18:01.985 --> 18:05.155
The answer was so simple.

18:05.155 --> 18:08.158
I was gonna predict that.

18:08.158 --> 18:09.591
You win.

18:12.428 --> 18:13.861
I've missed a step.

18:14.998 --> 18:18.001
He's got you on a pedestal...

18:18.001 --> 18:19.969
and me in his arms.

18:27.844 --> 18:31.881
My God, it's the bride
and the woman she'll never live up to.

18:31.881 --> 18:34.684
- Are you okay, honey?
- That would be us.

18:34.684 --> 18:37.353
Did she say the wrong thing again?
That is so in character.

18:37.353 --> 18:39.522
- I'm Julianne Potter.
- We'd be the vengeful sluts.

18:39.522 --> 18:43.693
- You can just call us eager.
- Have you sized up the groomsmen?

18:43.693 --> 18:47.697
- As maid of honor, you get first pick.
- Don't pick the short, hairy, tat one.

18:47.697 --> 18:50.200
- He's mine.
- Kimmy's a virgin.

18:50.200 --> 18:52.635
Is this Michael's Julianne?

18:52.635 --> 18:55.205
I'm Isabelle Wallace.

18:55.205 --> 18:58.003
My handsome new son
scarcely did you justice.

18:59.242 --> 19:02.712
My husband says
to scoot you to the ballpark...

19:02.712 --> 19:04.814
so you can hang with Michael.

19:04.814 --> 19:07.884
But first you have to meet
a lot of really old women.

19:07.884 --> 19:11.149
That is, it you've absorbed
enough profanity.

19:25.201 --> 19:26.703
Who ordered a beer?

19:26.703 --> 19:31.541
- Let me help you with that.
- You unwittingly imply I'm clumsy.

19:31.541 --> 19:34.244
Sorry. I was confusing you
with somebody I used to know.

19:34.244 --> 19:37.380
Julianne Potter, this is Hank and Eric
from Sport magazine.

19:37.380 --> 19:39.382
- Nice to meet you.
- They kindly gave me a job.

19:39.382 --> 19:42.018
- Hi, there.
- How do you do?

19:42.018 --> 19:45.288
And this is Walter,
my father-in-Law.

19:45.288 --> 19:47.757
Future father-in-Law.
''Comiskey''

19:47.757 --> 19:49.259
Thank you.

19:49.259 --> 19:51.887
If he gives you any grief,
come see me.

19:53.463 --> 19:57.267
- And this guy you know.
- Papa Joe.

19:57.267 --> 20:02.772
I told him to make you best man,
but he had to go with his baby brother.

20:02.772 --> 20:05.441
Best-looking guy
in any room.

20:05.441 --> 20:08.378
- Great to see you.
- That will do.

20:08.378 --> 20:11.614
- Scotty, that will do.
- Sorry.

20:11.614 --> 20:14.284
Remember, it is the duty
of the best man...

20:14.284 --> 20:17.587
to dance
with the maid of honor.

20:17.587 --> 20:20.123
Dance? You can't dance.

20:20.123 --> 20:25.060
- When did you Learn to dance?
- I've got moves you've never seen.

20:26.496 --> 20:28.327
You're an impostor.

20:29.966 --> 20:32.302
What did you do
with my best friend?

20:32.302 --> 20:35.805
''Chicago Tribune"
I'm still your best friend.

20:35.805 --> 20:38.467
You just haven't seen me
for awhile.

20:42.979 --> 20:47.417
Some people might find
that kind of perfection boring...

20:47.417 --> 20:50.653
- day after day, year after year.
- That's what I thought at first.

20:50.653 --> 20:52.822
How can you like someone
that perfect?

20:52.822 --> 20:56.492
No potential
for long-range Likeability.

20:56.492 --> 21:00.330
But then, she does have
a few good traits.

21:00.330 --> 21:01.831
- All right.
- Such as?

21:01.831 --> 21:04.133
They got him.

21:04.133 --> 21:06.669
When I hug her,
even in public...

21:06.669 --> 21:09.505
I don't have to let go
right away.

21:09.505 --> 21:12.008
She lets me hold her
as long as I want.

21:12.008 --> 21:16.012
- Batting second, the shortstop--
- What?

21:16.012 --> 21:19.182
- Nothing.
- I forgot.

21:19.182 --> 21:21.884
You and that yucky love stuff.

21:21.884 --> 21:24.020
You always get like that
when it gets sentimental.

21:24.020 --> 21:26.215
I do not.

21:27.890 --> 21:30.827
When we were--
When you and I were--

21:30.827 --> 21:32.954
- When we were--
